BATCH TRANSCRIPTION CREATE ADVANCED

  The `spx batch transcription create` command creates new
  transcription requests to transcribe remote audio streams.

USAGE: spx batch transcription create [...]

  CONNECTION                      (see: spx help batch connection)
    --key KEY                     (see: spx help batch key)
    --region REGION               (see: spx help batch region)

  CREATE
    --name NAME                   (see: spx help batch transcription name)
    --model URL                   (see: spx help batch transcription create model)
    --dataset URL                 (see: spx help batch transcription create dataset)
    --content URL                 (see: spx help batch transcription create content)
    --content @URLs.txt           (see: spx help batch transcription create content)
    --language LANGUAGE           (see: spx help batch transcription create language)

  PROPERTIES
    --diarization                 Identify two speakers in mono channel audio
    --word level timing           Add word level timestamps to the output
    --punctuation mode MODE       MODE: None, Dictated, Automatic or DictatedAndAutomatic(default)
    --profanity filter FILTER     FILTER: None, Masked(default), Removed, or Tags
    --property NAME=VALUE         (see: spx help batch transcription create properties)
    --properties @FILENAME        (see: spx help batch transcription create properties)
    --description DESCRIPTION     (see: spx help batch transcription description)
    --project URL                 (see: spx help batch transcription project)

  OUTPUT
    --output json FILENAME        (see: spx help batch output json)
    --output url @@FILE           (see: spx help batch output url)
    --output id @@FILE            (see: spx help batch output id)
    --wait [TIMEOUT]              (see: spx help batch transcription wait)

  PARALLEL PROCESSING
    --threads NUMBER              (see: spx help batch threads)
    --processes NUMBER            (see: spx help batch processes)

  ADVANCED
    --input path PATH             (see: spx help batch input path)
    --output path PATH            (see: spx help batch output path)
    --foreach in @FILENAME        (see: spx help batch foreach)
    --save FILENAME               (see: spx help batch save)
    --zip ZIPFILE                 (see: spx help batch zip)

